<section>
<section>
<h2>Propositional logic vs. English</h2>
<p>The connectives of propositional logic are intended to translate certain words of English. But the meanings we give to the connectives don't perfectly match up with the meanings of the associated English words.</p>

<ul>
<li class="fragment">It's possible that the truth conditions that propositional logic assigns to the connective don't match our intuitions about how the associated English word is used.</li>
<li class="fragment">We just have to remember that we are using the language of propositional logic, and the truth conditions it gives are <em>all there is</em> to the meaning of the co</li>
</ul>

</section>

